== Short Bio


Prof. *Wenqi Fan* is currently an Assistant Professor of the Department of Computing (COMP) & Department of Management and Marketing (MM), The Hong Kong Polytechnic University (PolyU). Before that, he was a Research Assistant Professor and a Postdoctoral Fellow at PolyU (2020-2023). He received his Ph.D. degree in computer science from the City University of Hong Kong (2017-2020), under the supervision of [https://www4.comp.polyu.edu.hk/~csqli/ *Prof. Qing LI*] and [http://www.cs.cityu.edu.hk/~jianwang/ *Prof. Jianping WANG*]. 
From 2018 to 2021, he was a  research scholar of [http://www.dse.cse.msu.edu Data Science and Engineering (DSE) Lab] at Michigan State University (MSU), under the supervision of [http://www.cse.msu.edu/~tangjili *Prof. Jiliang Tang*]. 
He is recognized as the *AI 2000 Most Influential Scholar Honorable Mention* ([./others/AI-2000-2022.png 2022], [./others/AI-2000-2023.png 2023], [./others/AI-2000-2024.png 2024], 2025) , and one of the World’s Top 2% Scientists by Stanford University (2023, 2024, 2025). 
His research has been supported by multiple government research fund agencies, including Hong Kong Research Grants Council (*RGC-GRF*), National Natural Science Foundation of China (*NSFC*), Hong Kong Innovation and Technology Commission (*ITF*), etc. 
He has published his research in highly ranked journals and top conference proceedings \[[https://scholar.google.com/citations?user=SQ9UbHIAAAAJ&hl=en  *Google Scholar*]\]. 



